{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Bond Glacier | other_name = | photo = Antarctica Map.png | photo_width = 250px | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Map of Antarctica, with Wilkes Land slightly to the right | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Bond Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = heavily crevassed | location = [[Wilkes Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|66|58|00|S|109|00|00|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Blunt Cove]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Bond Glacier''' ({{Coord|66|58|S|109|0|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a steep, heavily crevassed [[glacier]] to the west of [[Ivanoff Head]], flowing from the continental ice to [[Blunt Cove]] at the head of [[Vincennes Bay]]. It was mapped from air photos taken by [[U.S. Navy Operation Highjump]] (1946–47), and named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for Captain [[Charles A. Bond]], [[U.S. Navy]], commander of the expedition's Western Group.
