[[Image:FranzHubner.jpg|thumb|200px|Franz Hübner]]
'''Franz Hübner'''(18 November 1846 [[Drossen,Frankfurt|Drossen]], near [[Frankfurt an der Oder]] – 31 December 1877) was a [[Germany|German]] [[entomologist]]

Between 1875 and 1877 he collected insects for the [[Museum Godeffroy]] in [[Samoa]], [[Tonga]] and [[New Britain]].

