{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | name = ''Ilyobacter insuetus'' | image = | image_caption = | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Fusobacteria]] | classis = [[Fusobacteriia]] | subclassis =[[Fusobacteriales]] | ordo = [[Fusobacteriaceae]] | subordo = | genus = ''[[Ilyobacter]]'' | genus_authority = | species = '''''I. insuetus''''' | binomial = '''''Ilyobacter insuetus''''' | binomial_authority = Brune et al. 2002<ref name=Ilyobacter-insuetus>{{cite journal |last1=Parte |first1=A.C. |title=Ilyobacter |journal=www.bacterio.net |url=http://www.bacterio.net/ilyobacter.html}}</ref> | type_strain = ATCC BAA-291, DSM 6831, strain VenChi2<ref name=UniProt>{{cite journal |title=Ilyobacter insuetus |journal=www.uniprot.org |url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/167643 |language=en}}</ref> | subdivision = | synonyms = }}
'''''Ilyobacter insuetus''''' is a [[mesophilic]] and [[Anaerobic organism|anaerobic]] bacterium from the genus of ''[[Ilyobacter]]'' which has been isolated from marine [[anoxic sediments]] from [[Venice]] in [[Italy]].<ref name=Ilyobacter-insuetus/><ref name=UniProt/><ref>{{cite journal |title=Details: DSM-6831 |journal=www.dsmz.de |url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-6831.html |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Brune |first1=A |last2=Evers |first2=S |last3=Kaim |first3=G |last4=Ludwig |first4=W |last5=Schink |first5=B |title=Ilyobacter insuetus sp. nov., a fermentative bacterium specialized in the degradation of hydroaromatic compounds. |journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology |date=March 2002 |volume=52 |issue=Pt 2 |pages=429–32 |doi=10.1099/00207713-52-2-429 |pmid=11931152}}</ref>
