The '''Large Lakes Observatory''', located in [[Duluth, Minnesota]], studies the major lakes of the world.<ref>Gagnon, John (2012) ''Lake Superior Profiles: People on the Big Lake'' Wayne State University Press, Detroit, Michigan, [https://books.google.com/books?id=kShCwwBAG8QC&pg=PA128 page 128], {{ISBN|978-0-8143-3628-1}}</ref> The researchers focus on a variety of sciences including [[aquatic chemistry]], [[geochemistry]] and [[paleoclimatology]].



The ''Blue Heron'' is the LLO's research vessel.<ref>[http://www.d.umn.edu/llo/index.html Large Lakes Observatory]</ref>



