'''Lee Sung-yang''' ({{zh|c=李淳陽|p=Lǐ Chúnyáng}}, born 29 May 1922) is a Taiwanese entomologist. He was the subject of the 1975 [[BBC]] documentary ''The Insect World of Dr. Lee''. In [[Taiwan]], he is referred to as the "Taiwanese [[Jean Henri Fabre]]."

