{{Expert-subject|Physics|date=November 2008}}

The '''MacDowell–Mansouri action''' (named after S. W. MacDowell and Freydoon Mansouri) is an [[action (physics)|action]] that is used to derive [[Einstein's field equations]] of [[general relativity]].

==References==
*{{Cite journal |first=S. W. |last=MacDowell |first2=F. |last2=Mansouri |title=Unified geometric theory of gravity and supergravity |journal=[[Physical Review Letters|Phys. Rev. Lett.]] |volume=38 |issue=14 |year=1977 |pages=739–742 |doi=10.1103/PhysRevLett.38.739 |bibcode=1977PhRvL..38..739M}}
*{{Cite web |title=Derek Wise on Cartan Geometry and MacDowell–Mansouri Gravity |work=The n-Category Café |date=July 7, 2007 |url=http://golem.ph.utexas.edu/category/2007/07/derek_wise_on_cartan_geometry.html }}

{{DEFAULTSORT:MacDowell-Mansouri action}}
[[Category:General relativity]]


