{{Infobox journal | title = Society | cover = [[File:SocietyJournal.jpg]] | discipline = [[Sociology]] | abbreviation = Society | editor = Jonathan Imber | former_name = Transaction: Social Science and Modern SOCIETY | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]] | country = [[United States of America|USA]] | frequency = | history = 1962 — present | openaccess = no | impact= 0.188 | impact-year=2015 | website = https://www.springer.com/social+sciences/sociology/journal/12115 | ISSN = 0147-2011 }}
'''''Society''''' is a [[scientific journal]] that publishes discussions and research findings in the [[social science]]s and [[public policy]].
It was founded as ''Transaction: Social Science and Modern SOCIETY'' by [[Irving Louis Horowitz#Transactions Publishing and Society|Irving Louis Horowitz]] in 1962. It was published by [[Transaction Publishers]] for decades before being purchased by [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]]. Its chief editor is Jonathan Imber.
== Abstracting and indexing == ''Society'' is abstracted and indexed in the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2015 [[impact factor]] of 0.188.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Society |title=2015 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
