| classis = [[Synergistia]]
| ordo = [[Synergistales]]
| familia = [[Synergistaceae]]
| genus = ''[[Synergistes]]''
| species = '''''S. jonesii'''''
| species_authority = Allison et al. 1993
}}

'''''Synergistes jonesii''''' is a species of bacteria, the type species of its genus. It is a [[rumen]] bacterium that degrades toxic [[pyridinediol]]s. It is obligately anaerobic, [[gram-negative]] and rod-shaped.<ref name="AllisonMayberry1992">{{cite journal|last1=Allison|first1=Milton J.|last2=Mayberry|first2=Wiliam R.|last3=Mcsweeney|first3=Christopher S.|last4=Stahl|first4=David A.|title=Synergistes jonesii, gen. nov., sp.nov.: A Rumen Bacterium That Degrades Toxic Pyridinediols|journal=Systematic and Applied Microbiology|volume=15|issue=4|year=1992|pages=522–529|issn=0723-2020|doi=10.1016/S0723-2020(11)80111-6}}</ref>

